Directory contents
------------------

This directory contains the following files:

obsfile.lis    : observation parameters common to all observing modes
simfile.lis    : simulation parameters common to all observing modes
heatrunobs.lis : HEATRUN (flatfield) observation parameters
heatrunsim.lis : HEATRUN (flatfield) simulation parameters
stareobs.lis   : STARE observation parameters
staresim.lis   : STARE simulation parameters
dreamobs.lis   : DREAM observation parameters
dreamsim.lis   : DREAM simulation parameters
pongobs.lis    : PONG observation parameters
pongsim.lis    : PONG simulation parameters
README         : this file
candycanes.sdf : Example astronomical sky image

Input files for the simulator
-----------------------------

The simulator requires two input files: one containing `observation'
parameters, the other containing `simulation' parameters.  There is no
requirement for them to have a particular name. Some parameters are
common to all observing modes, while others are only meaningful to
particular modes.

The two most important files are `obsfile.lis' and `simfile.lis' which
contain all the parameters common to all observing modes.

The simulator tries to choose sensible default values when parameters
are not defined, but they will probably not be what you want so if in
doubt, keep all of the parameters given in the template files.

To carry out a simulation of a given observing mode, include the
necessary mode-specific parameters into obsfile.lis and simfile.lis
files. 

Note: the first step is to create flatfield (heatrun) files. Therefore
the first time the simulator is run should be to create those files
with a HEATRUN observing mode.
